NUMBER 2401
REGION 11
NAME Rainforest, understory
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Thick, tangled vegetation at the fringe near the beach gives way to the true jungle interior. The rich canopy above blocks most of the grey, rainy sky, and large drops where rain and drizzle have pooled plunk to the ground, leaving little craters in the soil beneath the seedling carpet. No other undergrowth survives here and the passage through the trees is an easy one.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 61
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
LIMITED_MOVEMENT
EXIT NW 2407
EXIT NE 2402
EXIT S 2778
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Hundreds of seedlings just taller than your feet cover the ground, awaiting life-giving light. Most will die, but perhaps one will grow to maturity if a nearby tree falls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SEARCH -1
	IFVAR JUNG1 ! TIM
		RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
		ADD DUMMY1 PER
		IFVAR DUMMY1 > 140
			EQUAL JUNG1 TIM
			NEWITEM 2 1681 ADJ1=1244 VAL2=5 VAL3=316 VAL5=7
			ECHO PLAYER After a careful search, you find a tricana seedling amongst the others.
			ECHO OTHERS %N found something!
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2402
REGION 11
NAME Rainforest, understory
*DESCRIPTION_START WINTER
An unusually tall tree dominates this little hollow, its buttresses easily ten feet high. Rivulets of water, captured by the leaves above in the last rain shower, stream down the mossy trunk. Straight and unmarred for an additional twenty feet, the trunk is marred by a large dark hole opening just below the crown.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 61
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
JUNGLE
EXIT N 2403
EXIT NW 2404
EXIT SW 2401
ITEM 0 336 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=87
